Spicules. (Fig. 6 A–G) Auxiliary subtylostyles straight and slender, some with faintly swollen heads, both smooth and/or microspined head 96.2–392 × 1–6.2 µm. Thick tylostyles straight or slightly bent, with smooth or microspined heads 119.6–410 × 5.2–28.6 µm. Acanthostyles are minutely spined all over, at times faintly spined, with tiny spines on head 52–120 × 2–10.4 µm. Palmate isochelae never twisted 12.2–18.2 µm. Wide oxhorn toxas, others not so, in two size categories that overlap: 20.8–222 µm and less than one micron to 5.2 µm (Measurements in
Tab. 2
).
